comment: Thomas (BOS) dislodges Leuer (DET) and affects his FOM.
Smart (BOS) sets the screen on Drummond (DET) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Crowder (BOS) clamps Drummond's (DET) arm, affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of DET possession is overturned and BOS is awarded possession.
There is no clear and conclusive evidence that Caldwell-Pope (DET) makes contact with Thomas (BOS) that affects his jump shot attempt.
Thomas (BOS) makes marginal contact with Jackson (DET) that does not affect his SQBR.
Horford (BOS) makes incidental contact with Harris (DET) that does not affect his SQBR.
Jerebko (BOS) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Harris (DET) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Horford (BOS) makes marginal contact with Caldwell-Pope (DET) following the screen.
Smart (BOS) makes incidental contact with Jackson (DET) that does not affect his SQBR.
Horford (BOS) maintains legal guarding position on the drive to the basket by Jackson (DET).
LHH shows Jerebko (BOS) make contact with Leuer's (DET) body, affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Smart (BOS) is the first player to touch the ball after causing it to go from the frontcourt to the backcourt while his team is in control of the ball.
Horford (BOS) maintains legal guarding position and blocks Jackson's (DET) shot attempt.
Drummond (DET) makes incidental contact with Jerebko (BOS).
Jackson (DET) commits a take foul on Thomas (BOS).
Thomas (BOS) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Smith (DET) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Smith (DET) commits a take foul on Thomas (BOS).
